That's only because we forced it on him.

607
00:22:19,810 --> 00:22:21,280
Doesn't he look great as one?

608
00:22:21,480 --> 00:22:23,310
- You won, so take the center. - Right.

609
00:22:23,750 --> 00:22:24,980
Really?

610
00:22:24,980 --> 00:22:26,720
You'll stand in the center, and Se Chan will join you.

611
00:22:26,720 --> 00:22:29,390
No way. He's not serving a strong look.

612
00:22:29,390 --> 00:22:30,820
Old man, step back.

613
00:22:32,490 --> 00:22:33,760
Ssaebssaeb, how about I do this?

614
00:22:33,760 --> 00:22:34,860
That's a great idea.

615
00:22:35,330 --> 00:22:36,730
- I love it. - Can you step back a little?

616
00:22:37,560 --> 00:22:38,830
I'll step back a little.

617
00:22:41,060 --> 00:22:42,300
I like how we're positioned.

618
00:22:42,430 --> 00:22:43,870
Even in that, he's trying to look good.

619
00:22:45,740 --> 00:22:47,770
- There we go. - He's trying to look good.

620
00:22:47,770 --> 00:22:49,940
- We're ready. - Here we go. One, two.

621
00:22:51,340 --> 00:22:53,410
- One, two. - I like how we're positioned.

622
00:22:53,580 --> 00:22:55,380
This is hilarious. What a mess.

623
00:22:57,210 --> 00:22:59,950
Why is Haha dressed up as his mom?

624
00:23:01,080 --> 00:23:03,690
Look at us trying to look good even in these silly costumes.

625
00:23:04,150 --> 00:23:05,590
Unbelievable.

626
00:23:11,700 --> 00:23:13,930
Running Man is rated 12 and up.

627
00:23:14,300 --> 00:23:16,070
- It's 15 and up. - Seok Jin!

628
00:23:16,300 --> 00:23:18,170
- Seriously? - Come on, old man.

629
00:23:18,170 --> 00:23:19,570
- Unbelievable. - Old man.

630
00:23:19,570 --> 00:23:21,200
- It's 15 and up. - Old man, come on.

631
00:23:21,200 --> 00:23:23,070
- Stop trying to steal the show. - It was changed a while ago.

632
00:23:23,140 --> 00:23:24,240
Seok Jin, come on!

633
00:23:24,370 --> 00:23:25,680
Is it 15 and up?

634
00:23:25,680 --> 00:23:27,010
- Yes. - It was changed.

635
00:23:30,950 --> 00:23:33,020
Get lucky this year.

636
00:23:35,750 --> 00:23:37,320
- We'll do that once more. - Sure.

637
00:23:38,420 --> 00:23:40,660
Lower your hand. Stop trying to look cute.

638
00:23:40,660 --> 00:23:41,960
- Stop it! - What are you doing?

639
00:23:41,960 --> 00:23:43,490
- What is that? - Why would you do that?

640
00:23:43,490 --> 00:23:45,530
- Let me look cute, will you? - Just stand still.

641
00:23:45,700 --> 00:23:47,700
- Just stick to your character. - Unbelievable.

642
00:23:48,030 --> 00:23:49,670
Don't cup your face.

643
00:23:50,500 --> 00:23:52,140
Why would you do that?

644
00:23:52,140 --> 00:23:53,670
- Stop it. - Look.

645
00:23:53,670 --> 00:23:54,840
- He's trying to cover his face. - Old man!

646
00:23:54,840 --> 00:23:57,070
- Let me look cute, will you? - Don't do that.

647
00:23:57,070 --> 00:23:58,410
- I look awful, that's all. - Lower your arm.

648
00:23:58,410 --> 00:24:00,310
- You look funnier without it. - Lower your arm.

649
00:24:00,310 --> 00:24:01,340
- Your makeup is the funniest. - Looking cool...

650
00:24:01,340 --> 00:24:02,850
- would actually be hilarious. - Your teeth should show.

651
00:24:05,380 --> 00:24:06,650
- All right. - Like this.

652
00:24:07,950 --> 00:24:09,090
- We're good. - Okay.

653
00:24:09,090 --> 00:24:10,250
Thank you.

654
00:24:10,720 --> 00:24:11,960
I'm the winner.

655
00:24:11,960 --> 00:24:14,060
I displayed royal dignity.

656
00:24:14,190 --> 00:24:16,190
Say "Running Man is rated 15 and up" and wave.

657
00:24:16,190 --> 00:24:17,860
Rated 15 and up, right?

658
00:24:17,860 --> 00:24:18,930
Yes. Here we go.

659
00:24:19,130 --> 00:24:20,130
Running Man is...

660
00:24:20,130 --> 00:24:22,870
- rated 15 and up. - Rated 15 and up.

661
00:24:23,030 --> 00:24:24,570
Go to bed early if you're 12.

662
00:24:24,570 --> 00:24:25,970
- Seok Jin! - Seok Jin, come on.

663
00:24:25,970 --> 00:24:28,040
- Stop that! - What's wrong with you?

664
00:24:28,040 --> 00:24:30,070
- They still watch the show. - What's his problem?

665
00:24:30,070 --> 00:24:31,210
It's way too early to go to bed.

666
00:24:31,210 --> 00:24:32,440
Who sleeps that early?

667
00:24:32,440 --> 00:24:33,910
- It's only 6pm. - Seok Jin, come on.

668
00:24:33,910 --> 00:24:35,180
- The show starts at 6pm. - Who sleeps at 6pm?

669
00:24:35,180 --> 00:24:36,210
Sorry about that.

670
00:24:36,210 --> 00:24:37,610
Let's go with "Get lucky this year."

671
00:24:37,610 --> 00:24:39,280
- Get lucky this year. - That's better.

672
00:24:39,320 --> 00:24:40,680
- Sure thing. - Here we go.

673
00:24:41,320 --> 00:24:42,320
Running Man is...

674
00:24:42,320 --> 00:24:44,150
- rated 15 and up. - Rated 15 and up.

675
00:24:44,150 --> 00:24:46,520
- Get lucky this year. - Get lucky!

676
00:24:47,190 --> 00:24:48,960
- That sounded rude. - Sorry about that.

677
00:24:48,960 --> 00:24:50,190
I got carried away.

678
00:24:50,190 --> 00:24:52,330
- Just stop it. - What's your problem?

679
00:24:52,330 --> 00:24:53,700
- What's with him? - I'm sorry.

680
00:24:53,700 --> 00:24:54,930
- Seok Jin, I'm cold. - Stop it.

681
00:24:54,930 --> 00:24:56,600
We'll get one without any improv.

682
00:24:56,600 --> 00:24:58,370
- Sure. That's your fault. - No improvising.

683
00:24:58,500 --> 00:25:00,270
It's not like his improv...

684
00:25:00,270 --> 00:25:02,640
- is even funny. - I know. It's not even funny.

685
00:25:03,240 --> 00:25:04,240
Running Man is...

686
00:25:04,240 --> 00:25:06,610
- rated 15 and up. - Rated 15 and up.

687
00:25:08,580 --> 00:25:09,850
- Cut. - Okay.

688
00:25:09,850 --> 00:25:12,720
- Good job. - He slipped in a laugh.

689
00:25:12,720 --> 00:25:13,720
- It's so cold. - He slipped in a laugh.

690
00:25:13,720 --> 00:25:14,750
Roll with it.

691
00:25:14,750 --> 00:25:16,890
You'll see later that it adds flavor.

692
00:25:17,090 --> 00:25:18,590
Are we staying dressed like this for the opening?

693
00:25:18,590 --> 00:25:19,590
Are we done?

694
00:25:19,860 --> 00:25:21,290
Hold on. How do I deal with this?

695
00:25:21,290 --> 00:25:22,730
I should just take it off.

696
00:25:22,790 --> 00:25:24,730
Hey, it's snow!

697
00:25:25,200 --> 00:25:26,660
She's pretending to be happy.

698
00:25:27,830 --> 00:25:29,430
- My gosh. - What on earth?

699
00:25:29,430 --> 00:25:30,470
Ji Hyo, wait.

700
00:25:31,130 --> 00:25:32,540
- It's snow! - What's gotten into you?

701
00:25:32,540 --> 00:25:33,540
Ji Hyo, wait.

702
00:25:33,540 --> 00:25:36,140
- It actually snowed hours ago. - The snow's a few hours old.

703
00:25:36,140 --> 00:25:38,540
Jae Seok, don't you just love the snow?

704
00:25:38,540 --> 00:25:41,210
You must've seen the snow on your way to work today.

705
00:25:41,210 --> 00:25:42,650
- Exactly. - So why...

706
00:25:42,650 --> 00:25:44,780
- I only just woke up. - You're only confusing us...

707
00:25:44,780 --> 00:25:45,850
- by keeping this up. - What do you mean?

708
00:25:45,850 --> 00:25:47,680
You were quiet in the green room,

709
00:25:48,020 --> 00:25:49,650
but suddenly you seemed ecstatic.

710
00:25:49,920 --> 00:25:51,520
- Are you forcing it? - You're throwing us off.

711
00:25:51,520 --> 00:25:53,890
- This is me doing my job. - Of course.

712
00:25:53,890 --> 00:25:55,230
It's snow!

713
00:25:56,930 --> 00:25:58,530
Today, we'll be joined...

714
00:25:58,530 --> 00:26:00,230
- by some guests. - I already saw them.

715
00:26:00,230 --> 00:26:01,460
Please come on in.

716
00:26:01,460 --> 00:26:02,500
- I already saw them. - Is that Jin Ho?

717
00:26:02,500 --> 00:26:04,270
- Hello! - It's Mimi.

718
00:26:04,270 --> 00:26:06,370
- Hi, everyone. - Hi, Mimi.

719
00:26:06,370 --> 00:26:08,100
Mimi!

720
00:26:08,140 --> 00:26:09,870
- Mimi! - Hi!

721
00:26:09,940 --> 00:26:11,140
Hi, Jin Ho.

722
00:26:11,140 --> 00:26:13,210
- Hi, Jae Seok. - Welcome, Jin Ho.

723
00:26:13,340 --> 00:26:14,540
- Hi. - Hey, Jin Ho.

724
00:26:14,540 --> 00:26:16,350
- It's good to see you. - Jin Ho's here.

725
00:26:16,710 --> 00:26:20,380
Steal from them, not from your own team.

726
00:26:20,780 --> 00:26:23,020
Why would you steal from your own team?

727
00:26:23,020 --> 00:26:24,050
Jin Ho, slowly.

728
00:26:24,050 --> 00:26:25,190
- His pronunciation's messed up. - Jin Ho.

729
00:26:25,190 --> 00:26:26,460
Caned with his hands,

730
00:26:26,460 --> 00:26:27,690
he told the sugar-sugar...

731
00:26:31,230 --> 00:26:32,960
- Who does this? - On the wedding invitation...

732
00:26:32,960 --> 00:26:34,400
is his account number!

733
00:26:35,370 --> 00:26:36,700
- Why... - Who cares?

734
00:26:36,700 --> 00:26:38,170
You won't come anyway!

735
00:26:38,170 --> 00:26:40,800
I don't think you'll come, so send something to congratulate me.

736
00:26:40,800 --> 00:26:43,710
- You didn't want to be a celeb? - I didn't. It wasn't my dream.

737
00:26:43,710 --> 00:26:45,510
- Originally... - What was your dream, then?

738
00:26:45,510 --> 00:26:47,140
To teach the Korean language and literature.

739
00:26:47,640 --> 00:26:50,250
- How, with that pronunciation? - You'll teach Korean...

740
00:26:50,250 --> 00:26:52,120
- with your pronunciation? - Honestly.

741
00:26:52,480 --> 00:26:53,520
Say "ga-gya-geo-gyeo."

742
00:26:53,520 --> 00:26:54,950
Ga-gya-gyeo, gyeo, gyo, gyo.

743
00:26:56,190 --> 00:26:57,390
The cap suits you so well.

744
00:26:57,390 --> 00:26:59,060
Yes, it's cute on Mimi.

745
00:26:59,820 --> 00:27:00,890
I like that look.

746
00:27:02,090 --> 00:27:04,030
- Mimi! - Hello.

747
00:27:04,430 --> 00:27:05,860
- Jin Ho. - Hello.

748
00:27:05,860 --> 00:27:07,900
- Jin Ho. - It has been a while.

749
00:27:07,930 --> 00:27:09,030
- What... - Jin Ho...

750
00:27:09,030 --> 00:27:11,170
- What happened? - What's wrong with your eye?

751
00:27:11,170 --> 00:27:12,200
You have a stye on your eye?

752
00:27:12,200 --> 00:27:13,700
- Eyelid surgery... - Is it a sty?

753
00:27:13,700 --> 00:27:15,270
- It's not double eyelid surgery. - Okay.

754
00:27:15,270 --> 00:27:17,240
I had surgery for lid ptosis last year.

755
00:27:17,240 --> 00:27:18,240
- Oh, dear. - You did?

756
00:27:18,240 --> 00:27:20,280
Yes. But it relapsed,

757
00:27:20,280 --> 00:27:21,580
so I had the surgery again,

758
00:27:21,580 --> 00:27:22,910
- Is that so? - and it's still swollen.

759
00:27:22,910 --> 00:27:23,950
It looks fine, though.

760
00:27:23,950 --> 00:27:25,750
- Don't film me. - It looks natural.

761
00:27:25,750 --> 00:27:26,950
- Why would you cover it? - It looks natural.

762
00:27:26,950 --> 00:27:29,150
Must you mention it as soon as I came on?

763
00:27:29,150 --> 00:27:31,150
- I haven't been here in a while. - Your eye looked different.

764
00:27:31,150 --> 00:27:32,660
- It's embarrassing. - You should've worn glasses.

765
00:27:32,660 --> 00:27:34,060
Did you do just one eye?

766
00:27:34,060 --> 00:27:35,090
No, he did both eyes.

767
00:27:35,090 --> 00:27:36,390
I did both eyes at first.

768
00:27:36,390 --> 00:27:37,390
Your eyes weren't the same size.

769
00:27:37,390 --> 00:27:39,960
They were, but this time, they operated on just this eye.

770
00:27:39,960 --> 00:27:42,300
You ended up getting the surgery done twice.

771
00:27:42,300 --> 00:27:44,570
- It so happened. - You and the number two...

772
00:27:44,570 --> 00:27:47,170
- You really... - I do everything twice.

773
00:27:47,170 --> 00:27:48,540
It looks like a mosquito bit him.

774
00:27:48,540 --> 00:27:49,640
Gosh.

775
00:27:49,640 --> 00:27:50,770
A mosquito bit him on the eye...

776
00:27:50,770 --> 00:27:53,180
Mimi and Jin Ho are here,

777
00:27:53,180 --> 00:27:54,580
so today's special...

778
00:27:54,580 --> 00:27:55,580
It'll be funny!

779
00:27:55,580 --> 00:27:57,180
It's a diction special.

780
00:27:57,180 --> 00:27:58,880
- Yes. - It's a diction special.

781
00:27:58,880 --> 00:28:01,680
It'll be about diction, but neither of them is bright.

782
00:28:01,680 --> 00:28:02,790
Yes, that's true.

783
00:28:02,790 --> 00:28:04,490
- We're clever. - It'll be hard to understand.

784
00:28:04,490 --> 00:28:05,660
How have you been?

785
00:28:05,660 --> 00:28:07,560
I've been working hard.

786
00:28:07,560 --> 00:28:09,230
- Have you? - Yes. Let's work.

787
00:28:09,230 --> 00:28:10,530
- Good luck. - Okay.

788
00:28:10,590 --> 00:28:13,230
The episode we're filming today...

789
00:28:13,230 --> 00:28:15,230
will air in the second week...

790
00:28:15,230 --> 00:28:16,430
- of February. - I see.

791
00:28:16,430 --> 00:28:17,600
Jin Ho.

792
00:28:17,600 --> 00:28:18,600
- So... - That's why Jin Ho's here.

793
00:28:18,600 --> 00:28:22,010
Jin Ho embodies the number two, and Mimi's name has...

794
00:28:22,010 --> 00:28:24,270
